Remove the root and dark green part of the @leek{1}. Halve and thinly slice into half moons. Remove the ends from the @courgette{1}, quarter lengthways, then chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Remove the @flat leaf parsley{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Zest the @lemon{1/2}. Shape the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} into balls (six per person).

Boil your kettle. Heat a splash of @oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the leek and a pinch of @salt and @ground black pepper{}. Cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{3-5%minutes}. Once soft, add the garlic and courgette, stir and cook for ~{2%minutes} before stirring in the @orzo{180%g} as well.

Pour the boiling @water{500%ml}(for the orzo) into a #measuring jug{} and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1} until dissolved. Pour the stock into the orzo mix, bring to a simmer and cook until the orzo is tender, about ~{10%minutes}. Add more water if it all evaporates before the orzo is cooked. Stir every minute or so to ensure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan!

While the orzotto cooks, heat a splash of @oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the meatballs and fry until browned on the outside and cooked in the middle, ~{9-10%minutes}. Turn every couple of mins and lower the heat if they are browning too quickly.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

When the orzo is cooked, remove from the heat and stir in the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated), lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice and three-quarters of the basil. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice as necessary.

Spoon the orzotto into #bowls{} and top with the meatballs. Crumble over the @feta cheese{100%g}, and sprinkle on the remaining basil. Enjoy!